    "created_at": "2012-02-15T21:36:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-02-15T21:36:25Z",
    "body": "We can define negative shifts as \"positive in the opposite direction\" or such, don't need to be bound by LLVM here. I'd prefer to support them, but agree that we should probably accept a wide variety of types for shift-amount.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
