    "created_at": "2012-02-15T22:31:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-02-15T22:31:10Z",
    "body": "Having the common case `x >> y` be safe and well-defined seems like a good idea, especially because the shift amount is so often a constant. You all could hide unsafe_shift_left/right intrinsics somewhere that map directly to the LLVM instructions.\n",
